# Solving the H√∂lder Inequality Problem in Lean 4

To solve the given problem in Lean 4, we need to prove the H√∂lder inequality for the product of finitely many functions. The specific goal is to show that for a nonempty finite set `s` of indices `őĻ`, and functions `p : őĻ ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0` (with `p i ‚Č† 0` for all `i`), `f : őĻ ‚Üí őĪ ‚Üí ūĚēú` (where `őĪ` is a discrete space and `ūĚēú` is a real closed field), and a weight `q : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0` satisfying `‚ąĎ i ‚ąą s, (p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = q‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`, we have:

`‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i]`

This is a direct application of the H√∂lder inequality for products, which states that for conjugate exponents `p‚āĀ, ..., p‚āô` and weights `w‚āĀ, ..., w‚āô` such that `‚ąĎ wŠĶĘ = 1`, we have `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ xŠĶĘ‚ÄĖ^(‚ąĎ wŠĶĘ) ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ ‚ÄĖxŠĶĘ‚ÄĖ^wŠĶĘ`.

In our case, we have `n = |s|` terms. The exponents are `pŠĶĘ` for `i ‚ąą s`. The weights are `(pŠĶĘ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ / (‚ąĎ_{j ‚ąą s} (p‚Īľ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)` for `i ‚ąą s`. These weights sum to 1 by construction. The inequality then gives:

`‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, f i‚ÄĖ^(‚ąĎ i ‚ąą s, (p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ^((p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ / (‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ))`

Since `q = (‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`, and `p i ‚Č† 0`, we have `‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ^((p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ / (‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)) = ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ^(p i / q)`. Therefore:

`‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, f i‚ÄĖ^q‚ĀĽ¬Ļ ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ^(p i / q)`

Raising both sides to the power of `q` (which is positive since `q = ‚ąĎ ... > 0` as all terms are positive and `s` is nonempty), we get:

`‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, f i‚ÄĖ ‚Č§ (‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ^(p i / q)) ^ q = ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, (‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ^(p i / q)) ^ q = ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ^p i`

This is exactly the desired inequality: `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i]`.

