  any_goals intro a; dsimp
  any_goals positivity
  have := hpqr.holderConjugate_div_div _ _ _ (mod_cast hr‚āÄ) ENNReal.coe_ne_top
  exact wInner_cWeight_le_cLpNorm_mul_cLpNorm _ _

/-- **H√∂lder's inequality**, binary case. -/
lemma cL1Norm_mul_le (p q : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) [hpq : ENNReal.HolderConjugate p q] :
    ‚ÄĖf * g‚ÄĖ‚āô_[1] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p] * ‚ÄĖg‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] := cLpNorm_mul_le _ _ one_ne_zero

/-- **H√∂lder's inequality**, finitary case. -/
lemma cLpNorm_prod_le {őĻ : Type*} {s : Finset őĻ} (hs : s.Nonempty) {p : őĻ ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0} (hp : ‚ąÄ i, p i ‚Č† 0)
    (q : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0) (hpq : ‚ąĎ i ‚ąą s, ((p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) = (q : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) (f : őĻ ‚Üí őĪ ‚Üí ūĚēú) :
    ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] := by
  induction hs using Finset.Nonempty.cons_induction generalizing q with
  | singleton => simp_all
  | cons i s hi hs ih =>
  simp_rw [prod_cons]
  rw [sum_cons, ‚Üź inv_inv (‚ąĎ _ ‚ąą _, _)] at hpq
  have : ENNReal.HolderTriple (p i) ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ i ‚ąą s, (p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ q := ‚ü®sorry‚ü©
```

We need to complete the inductive step. Let's look at the goal state:

```tactics
‚äĘ (‚ÜĎ(p i))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + (‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ i ‚ąą s, (p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ÜĎq)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ
```

This is exactly the equation we need to apply the Holder inequality. Let's complete the proof:

```tactics
  have h1 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ x ‚ąą s, (p x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p x] := by
    apply ih
    all_goals try { 
      simp_all [ENNReal.coe_inv, ENNReal.coe_add]
      <;> try { linarith }
    }
    all_goals try { 
      tauto
    }
```

Now we need to show:
`‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x * f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ (‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p x]) * ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i]`
where `q` satisfies `‚ąĎ x ‚ąą s, (p x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą s, (p x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ‚ĀĽ¬Ļ` and `p i ‚Č† 0`.

We have:
`q = (p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą s, (p x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`
Let `q' = (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą s, (p x)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`. Then `q = (p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + q'`.
We have `h1 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q'] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p x]`.

Now we need to relate `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x * f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q]` to `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q']`.
`‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x * f i = (‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x) * f i`
So `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x * f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] = ‚ÄĖ(‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x) * f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q]`
Using the property `‚ÄĖa * b‚ÄĖ = ‚ÄĖa‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖb‚ÄĖ` for `a, b` in a normed space:
`‚ÄĖ(‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x) * f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] = ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] * ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_`

We need to show:
`‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] * ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_ ‚Č§ (‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p x]) * ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_`

This follows from the inductive hypothesis `h1` applied to `q'`:
`‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q'] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p x]`
Multiplying both sides by `‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_` (which is non-negative):
`‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q'] * ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_ ‚Č§ (‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p x]) * ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_`

So we need to show `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] = ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q']`.
This follows from the fact that `q = q'` when `p i = ‚ąě`. But in our case, `p i` is finite.
Wait, no. We have `q = (p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + q'`. So `q` is different from `q'`.
But we have the property `‚ÄĖa‚ÄĖ_q = ‚ÄĖa‚ÄĖ_{q'}` when `q = q'`? No.
But we have `‚ÄĖa * b‚ÄĖ = ‚ÄĖa‚ÄĖ * ‚ÄĖb‚ÄĖ`. So we need to show `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] = ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ x ‚ąą s, f x‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q']`.
