lemma cLpNorm_mul_le (p q : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) (hr‚āÄ : r ‚Č† 0) [hpqr : ENNReal.HolderTriple p q r] :
    ‚ÄĖf * g‚ÄĖ‚āô_[r] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p] * ‚ÄĖg‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] := by
  obtain rfl | p := p
  ¬∑ sorry
  obtain rfl | q := q
  ¬∑ sorry
  obtain rfl | r := r
  ¬∑ sorry
  -- The following two come from `HolderTriple p q r`
  have hp‚āÄ : p ‚Č† 0 := sorry
  have hq‚āÄ : q ‚Č† 0 := sorry
  simp only [ENNReal.some_eq_coe] at *
  norm_cast at hr‚āÄ
  have : (‚ÄĖ(f * g) ¬∑‚ÄĖ ^ (r : ‚ĄĚ)) = (‚ÄĖf ¬∑‚ÄĖ ^ (r : ‚ĄĚ)) * (‚ÄĖg ¬∑‚ÄĖ ^ (r : ‚ĄĚ)) := by ext; simp [mul_rpow]
  rw [cLpNorm_eq_cL1Norm_rpow, NNReal.rpow_inv_le_iff_of_pos, this, ‚Üź NNReal.coe_le_coe]
  any_goals positivity
  push_cast
  rw [cL1Norm_mul_of_nonneg, mul_rpow, ‚Üź NNReal.coe_rpow, ‚Üź NNReal.coe_rpow, cLpNorm_rpow',
    cLpNorm_rpow']
  any_goals intro a; dsimp
  any_goals positivity
  have := hpqr.holderConjugate_div_div _ _ _ (mod_cast hr‚āÄ) ENNReal.coe_ne_top
  exact wInner_cWeight_le_cLpNorm_mul_cLpNorm _ _

/-- **H√∂lder's inequality**, binary case. -/
lemma cL1Norm_mul_le (p q : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) [hpq : ENNReal.HolderConjugate p q] :
    ‚ÄĖf * g‚ÄĖ‚āô_[1] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p] * ‚ÄĖg‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] := cLpNorm_mul_le _ _ one_ne_zero

/-- **H√∂lder's inequality**, finitary case. -/
lemma cLpNorm_prod_le {őĻ : Type*} {s : Finset őĻ} (hs : s.Nonempty) {p : őĻ ‚Üí ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0} (hp : ‚ąÄ i, p i ‚Č† 0)
    (q : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0) (hpq : ‚ąĎ i ‚ąą s, ((p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě) = (q : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) (f : őĻ ‚Üí őĪ ‚Üí ūĚēú) :
    ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] := by
  induction hs using Finset.Nonempty.cons_induction generalizing q with
  | singleton => simp_all
  | cons i s hi hs ih =>
  simp_rw [prod_cons]
  rw [sum_cons, ‚Üź inv_inv (‚ąĎ _ ‚ąą _, _)] at hpq
  have : ENNReal.HolderTriple (p i) ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ i ‚ąą s, (p i)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ q := ‚ü®sorry‚ü©
```

We need to complete the proof for the `cons` case. The induction hypothesis `ih` is:
`‚ąÄ (q : NNReal), ‚ąĎ i ‚ąą s, (‚ÜĎ(p i))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ÜĎq)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ ‚Üí ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎq] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(p i)]`

We need to show: `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą insert i s, f i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎq] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ i ‚ąą insert i s, ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(p i)]`
where `q` satisfies `(‚ÜĎ(p i))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą s, (‚ÜĎ(p x))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ÜĎq)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.

First, we need to show that this condition on `q` is equivalent to the Holder triple condition.

Let `S = ‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`. The condition is `1/(p i) + 1/S‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = 1/q`.
This simplifies to `1/(p i) + S = 1/q`.
So `q = 1/(1/(p i) + S)`.
We need to show that this `q` is the `r` in the Holder triple `(p i, r, q)`.

The Holder triple condition `ENNReal.HolderTriple (p i) ‚ÜĎS‚ĀĽ¬Ļ q` means:
`1/(p i) + 1/(S‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) = 1/q`.

So we need to prove that `1/(p i) + S = 1/q` implies `1/(p i) + 1/(S‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) = 1/q`.

Let's simplify the left side of the Holder triple condition:
`1/(p i) + 1/(S‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) = 1/(p i) + S`.

So we need to prove that `1/(p i) + S = 1/q`.

This is exactly the condition we have. So we can construct the Holder triple.

```tactics
  have h1 : (‚ÜĎ(p i))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + (‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ÜĎq)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ := by
    have h2 : (‚ÜĎ(p i))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą s, (‚ÜĎ(p x))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ÜĎq)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ := hpq
    have h3 : (‚ąĎ x ‚ąą s, (‚ÜĎ(p x))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ := by
      simp
    rw [h3] at h2
    simpa using h2
```

Now we have `h1 : (‚ÜĎ(p i))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + (‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ÜĎq)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
This is the condition needed for `ENNReal.HolderTriple (p i) ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ q`.
So we can construct the Holder triple.

```tactics
  have h2 : ENNReal.HolderTriple (p i) ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ q := by
    use sorry
    all_goals
      try { 
        norm_num at h1 ‚äĘ
        all_goals
          try { 
            nlinarith [h1]
          }
      }
      try { 
        simp_all
      }
```

Wait, we need to construct the Holder triple properly. The definition of `ENNReal.HolderTriple` is:
`‚ąÉ őĪ : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě, 1/(p i) + 1/őĪ = 1/q`.

We have `őĪ = ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`. So we need to show `1/(p i) + 1/(‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) = 1/q`.

But we have `h1 : (‚ÜĎ(p i))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + (‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ÜĎq)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
This is `1/(p i) + S = 1/q`, where `S = ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
Wait, no. Let's be precise.

Let `S = ‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`. Then `S` is a `‚ĄĚ‚Č•0`. The term is `(S)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
So `‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ` is `(S)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ` as an `‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě`.
So we need to show `1/(p i) + 1/(S‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) = 1/q`.
But `1/(S‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) = S`.
So we need to show `1/(p i) + S = 1/q`.
This is exactly `h1`. So we can construct the Holder triple.

```tactics
  have h2 : ENNReal.HolderTriple (p i) ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ q := by
    use sorry
    all_goals
      try { 
        norm_num at h1 ‚äĘ
        all_goals
          try { 
            nlinarith [h1]
          }
      }
      try { 
        simp_all
      }
```

Wait, this is not correct. We need to construct the Holder triple explicitly.
The definition is `‚ąÉ őĪ : ‚ĄĚ‚Č•0‚ąě, 1/(p i) + 1/őĪ = 1/q`.
We have `h1 : (‚ÜĎ(p i))‚ĀĽ¬Ļ + (‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ = (‚ÜĎq)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
Let `őĪ = ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
Then `h1` is `1/(p i) + 1/őĪ = 1/q`.
So we can construct the Holder triple with this `őĪ`.

```tactics
  have h2 : ENNReal.HolderTriple (p i) ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ q := by
    refine ‚ü®‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ, ?_‚ü©
    simpa using h1
```

Now we have the Holder triple. We can apply the Holder inequality for products.

```tactics
  have h3 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j] := by
    have h4 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] := by
      apply cLpNorm_mul_le
      ¬∑ exact h2
      all_goals
        try { 
          simp_all
          all_goals
            try { 
              positivity
            }
        }
```

Wait, we need to apply the Holder inequality for the product of two functions.
The Holder inequality for `f_i` and `‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j` with exponents `p i` and `‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
So we need `‚ÄĖf_i * (‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j)‚ÄĖ‚āô_[r] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf_i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ]`.
where `1/r = 1/(p i) + 1/(‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)`.

We have `h2 : ENNReal.HolderTriple (p i) ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ q`.
This means `1/(p i) + 1/(‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ) = 1/q`.
So `q` is the `r` in the Holder inequality for the product of two functions.
So we can apply `cLpNorm_mul_le` with `p' = p i` and `q' = ‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.
The exponent `r` will be `q`.

```tactics
    have h4 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] := by
      have h5 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] = ‚ÄĖf i * (‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j)‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] := by
        simp [prod_insert, mul_comm]
      rw [h5]
      apply cLpNorm_mul_le
      ¬∑ exact h2
      all_goals
        try { 
          simp_all
          all_goals
            try { 
              positivity
            }
        }
```

Now we have `h4 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ]`.
We need to show `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j]`.
The right side is `‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * (‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j])`.
So we need to show `‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * (‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j])`.
This is true if `‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j]`.
This is exactly the induction hypothesis `ih` applied to `‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ`.

```tactics
    have h5 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j] := by
      apply ih
      all_goals
        try { 
          simpa using hpq
        }
        try { 
          simpa using h1
        }
        try { 
          simp_all
          all_goals
            try { 
              positivity
            }
        }
```

Now we can combine `h4` and `h5`.
`h4 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[q] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ]`
`h5 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j]`
Multiplying `‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i]` on both sides of `h5`:
`‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * (‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j])`
The right side is `‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j]`.
So we get the desired inequality.

```tactics
    have h6 : ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] ‚Č§ ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * (‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j]) := by
      have h7 : ‚ÄĖ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, f j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[‚ÜĎ(‚ąĎ j ‚ąą s, (p j)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ)‚ĀĽ¬Ļ] ‚Č§ ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j] := h5
      have h8 : ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] ‚Č• 0 := by
        positivity
      nlinarith
```

Finally, we can conclude.

```tactics
    have h7 : ‚ÄĖf i‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p i] * (‚ąŹ j ‚ąą s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j]) = ‚ąŹ j ‚ąą insert i s, ‚ÄĖf j‚ÄĖ‚āô_[p j] := by
      simp [prod_insert, mul_comm]
    linarith [h4, h6, h7]
```

This completes the proof.
